# Leg (parliamentary business)

**User-facing name:** **Leg** — Swiss Parliament business (sessions, motions, publications, hearings). Not a personal calendar. Internal table/API names still use `calendar_events` / `calendar_event` for compatibility with 0.4 data and the Magnitu `entry_type` enum.

Events are treated like entries — scored by the recipe engine (pending Slice 5 port), displayed in the dashboard timeline, with forward-looking dates.

## Architecture (0.5)

- **Table:** `calendar_events` (`source`, `external_id`, `title`, `description`, `content`, `event_date`, `event_end_date`, `event_type`, `status`, `council`, `url`, `metadata JSON`, `fetched_at`). Schema unchanged from 0.4 — plugins write via repository only.
- **Entry type:** `calendar_event` in `entry_scores` and `magnitu_labels` ENUMs. **Do not rename.**
- **Controller:** `Seismo\Controller\LegController` (`src/Controller/LegController.php`) — orchestration only, no SQL. Routes: `?action=leg`, `?action=refresh_parl_ch`, `?action=save_leg_parl_ch`. Legacy `?action=calendar` is aliased to `LegController::show`.
- **View:** `views/leg.php` — date-grouped, future-first, status / council / event-type pills.
- **Plugin (fetcher):** `Seismo\Plugin\ParlCh\ParlChPlugin` (`src/Plugin/ParlCh/ParlChPlugin.php`) — implements `SourceFetcherInterface`, **no SQL**. Returns normalised arrays for the `calendar_event` family.
- **Repository:** `Seismo\Repository\CalendarEventRepository` (`src/Repository/CalendarEventRepository.php`) — the only place `calendar_events` SQL lives. `entryTable('calendar_events')` everywhere. Transactional `upsertBatch()`. `prune()` is a no-op (Leg unlimited per default retention policy). `upsertBatch()` / `prune()` throw if `isSatellite()`.
- **Config:** `calendar_config.json` next to `bootstrap.php` (gitignored; `calendar_config.example.json` is the committed shape), read/written by `Seismo\Config\CalendarConfigStore`. Plugin blocks keyed by `SourceFetcherInterface::getConfigKey()`.
- **Settings surface:** In 0.5, per-plugin settings are rendered inline on the Leg page (`views/leg.php`) and Diagnostics page. No separate settings page ported yet — the 0.4 `?action=settings&tab=leg` tab graduates in a later slice if still needed.

## Data sources

Currently implemented:

- **parliament_ch** — Swiss Parliament OData API (`ws.parlament.ch/odata.svc`). Fetches Business items (motions, interpellations, postulates, initiatives) and Session periods. Plugin id: `parl_ch`. Throttle: 4 hours via `getMinIntervalSeconds()`.

Adding a new Leg source = one new `src/Plugin/<Name>/` folder implementing `SourceFetcherInterface`, one line in `PluginRegistry`, a new config block keyed by `getConfigKey()` in `calendar_config.json`. The repository, page, and cron automatically pick it up. No controller / view / cron changes per source. See `core-plugin-architecture.mdc`.

## IMPORTANT: Magnitu API exclusion (intentional)

**Leg rows (`calendar_event`) are deliberately excluded from all Magnitu API endpoints.** This was done in 0.4 so the feature could be tested in Seismo before Magnitu / Magnitu Mini trains on the data. The exclusions must be preserved when the Magnitu controller is ported in **Slice 5**. In the 0.4 reference instance the rule lives in `controllers/magnitu.php`:

1. `handleMagnituEntries` — calendar block is commented out; `calendar_event` entries are NOT exported.
2. `handleMagnituScores` — validation whitelist is `['feed_item', 'email', 'lex_item']` only; Magnitu cannot push `calendar_event` scores.
3. `handleMagnituLabels` — same whitelist; Magnitu cannot push `calendar_event` labels.
4. `handleMagnituStatus` — entry counts and score counts filter out `calendar_event` rows.

In 0.5 the port will land in `Seismo\Controller\MagnituController` with the same four exclusions; see the Slice 5 definition of done in `docs/consolidation-plan.md`.

**To re-enable** when ready (future, explicit user decision):

- `handleMagnituEntries`: uncomment the calendar events block (search for "Calendar events are excluded from the Magnitu API").
- `handleMagnituScores`: add `'calendar_event'` back to the `in_array()` check.
- `handleMagnituLabels`: add `'calendar_event'` back to the `in_array()` check.
- `handleMagnituStatus`: remove the `AND entry_type != 'calendar_event'` filters, re-add the Leg count to totals.

**What still works internally** (and must keep working through 0.5 ports):

- Recipe scoring via `rescoreCalendarEvents()` (0.4 name — will become a method on the Slice-5 scoring service). Called from `magnituRescore()` and whenever `calendar_events` is refreshed.
- Scores display in: dashboard timeline, Leg page, Magnitu investigation-leads page, AI unified view.
- `RefreshAllService::runAll()` refreshes Leg data alongside all other plugin sources; the same code path handles the 0.4-equivalent of `handleRefreshAll`.

## Rules when changing Leg / calendar_events

- **Do NOT add `calendar_event` to the Magnitu API whitelist without explicit approval** — training on incomplete / untested data could degrade the model. This is the load-bearing reason the rule exists.
- The `entry_type` value `calendar_event` is already in the DB ENUM — no schema change needed to re-enable.
- Parliament CH API uses OData v2 format — dates may come as `/Date(timestamp)/` strings (handled inside `ParlChPlugin`, not at the repository layer).
- Leg entries sort **ASC** by `event_date` (future first), unlike all other entry types which sort DESC (newest first). The dashboard timeline merge respects this when surfacing Leg rows alongside feeds / lex / emails.
- When adding Leg rows to the dashboard timeline, they get forward-looking date labels ("today", "tomorrow", "in 5d") — see the calendar handling in `views/partials/dashboard_entry_loop.php`.
- All `calendar_events` reads in non-Leg code paths must go through `entryTable('calendar_events')` so satellite mode keeps working. Writes live in `CalendarEventRepository` only; satellites short-circuit before any write is attempted.
